cs.MM, cs.CR, cs.IR, cs.CV, cs.DC 

The paper discusses techniques for hiding information in multimedia and non-multimedia files, which suggests that it could belong to the Computer Science sub-categories of Multimedia (cs.MM), Cryptography and Security (cs.CR), Information Retrieval (cs.IR), Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV), and Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). However, since the paper primarily focuses on steganography and information hiding, cs.MM and cs.CR are the most likely sub-categories.
